{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A static prompt-template lint check rejects phase-specific instruction leakage copied from SKILL.md.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The failure boundary is local lint logic over template text (pattern/AST/rule matching). No real harness wiring or model call is required to expose leakage in a template artifact.","test_description":"Call the lint rule directly with a template fixture containing a verbatim phase-instruction fragment copied from SKILL.md and assert it returns a hard failure with rule id/location; include a near-miss fixture to verify it does not overfire.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The fully assembled prompt produced by the real test harness (after interpolation/fixtures) still contains no phase-instruction leakage.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Leakage can be introduced only when multiple local modules combine template, fixtures, and interpolation. Unit tests of the linter/template alone can miss assembly-time regressions.","test_description":"Run the real prompt-assembly path used by smoke tests with representative fixtures, capture the final prompt string, and assert no forbidden phase-instruction spans (or semantic equivalents) are present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.83,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The test invocation loads skill context from the plugin/skill files and validates behavior from that context rather than from hard-coded prompt rules.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a module-boundary failure: loader + file-backed skill source + prompt builder + invocation config. A pure unit test cannot prove the invocation is actually file-driven.","test_description":"Execute the test invocation through the real harness with a controlled skill file containing a unique sentinel instruction; assert the assembled context includes file-derived content and the test logic does not inject equivalent hard-coded rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If the relevant SKILL.md section is removed or degraded, the behavioral test fails with the same user-style prompt.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The claimed guarantee is behavioral dependence on skill content quality under the same prompt. That depends on real model output quality/sensitivity, which can vary run-to-run; mocks would hide this.","test_description":"Run the same user-style prompt against the real model twice: once with intact SKILL.md and once with a degraded/removed target section; assert pass under intact skill and fail under degraded skill using the same structured rubric and retry policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is ordering and data-flow across model client, artifact writer, and parser modules. A local function test is insufficient to catch pipeline ordering regressions.","test_description":"Invoke the real local pipeline with a response that would break parsing; assert a raw-output artifact is written first (with timestamp/run id), then parsing fails, and artifact contents match the pre-parse payload.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Assertions verify structured behavior (for example field placement or schema shape), not mere keyword presence that could come from prompt echoing.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The core failure boundary is assertion logic quality. You can expose false positives with crafted fixtures without real harness or model I/O.","test_description":"Test the assertion helper/rubric with two canned outputs: one keyword-echo string lacking required structure and one correctly structured payload; assert fail on echo and pass on structured output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
